    {
      "id": "1b8b220a_062e555b",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/rest/provider/HealthCheckProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 72,
      "message": "Got it, yeah we have root policy type. \nBut it really doesn't make the query quicker as the entire ToscaServiceTemplate will be fetched and parsed even for this.\n\nTake a look at line 320 or 504 here - https://github.com/onap/policy-models/blob/master/models-tosca/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/tosca/simple/provider/SimpleToscaProvider.java\n\nRegarding api's we only have below choices:\n1) Fetch policy types (all, all versions of a policy type, latest version of a policy type)\n2) Fetch policy (all, all versions of a policy, specific version of a policy, latest version of a policy)\n\nI can go for a query with specific name & version of policy type (which is expected to be there always), but that will add more processing time at the application level with no benefits at db level.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3239,
        "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
        "username": "ramverma"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-20 14:51:06.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "92dfb971_3c43def4",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
