      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/rest/provider/HealthCheckProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 72,
      "message": "oh, puke.  Well, we could just query the policy deployment or statistics table, but those aren't really relevant to API, so I guess we can just leave it this way for now.  Wonder if there's a way to just ask it to check the connection?  (Could add a method to the provider and the PfDao)?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-20 15:05:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1b8b220a_062e555b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
